\u8216\'3fWithout a cross-appeal, an appellee may \u8216\'3furge in support of a decree any matter appearing in the record although his argument may involve an attack upon the reasoning of the lower court or an insistence upon matter overlooked or ignored by it.\u8217\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1924124102&pubNum=708&originatingDoc=I0a4069429bf011d991d0cc6b54f12d4d&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_708_564&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.Search)#co_pp_sp_708_564" }{\fldrslt 
